                {
                    "flow": [
                        {
                            "id": 9,
                            "module": "gemini-ai:createACompletionGeminiPro",
                            "version": 1,
                            "parameters": {
                                "__IMTCONN__": 7186100
                            },
                            "mapper": {
                                "model": "gemini-2.5-flash",
                                "contents": [
                                    {
                                        "role": "user",
                                        "parts": [
                                            {
                                                "text": "\"Act as a professional meeting assistant. I will provide you with a meeting transcript that includes timestamps and speaker names. Your goal is to generate a structured, scannable summary that captures the essence of the conversation.\n\nPlease organize the summary using the following format:\n\nHeader: Title of the meeting and date (if available).\n\nMeeting Purpose: A 1-sentence description of why the meeting took place.\n\nKey Takeaways: A bulleted list of the 3-5 most important high-level outcomes or philosophies discussed.\n\nTopics (Detailed Breakdown): Use bold headings for each major topic. Under each heading, provide a concise explanation of the discussion, including specific features, problems, or solutions mentioned.\n\nNext Steps: A clear list of action items or follow-up tasks identified in the transcript.\n\nAnnotations (Highlights/Bookmarks): Extract specific moments marked as 'HIGHLIGHT' or 'BOOKMARK' in the transcript. Provide the title of the highlight and a brief 1-sentence summary of what happened during that specific clip.\n\nWriting Guidelines:\n\nBe Concise: Use bullet points and avoid dense paragraphs.\n\nBe Objective: Summarize what was said without adding external commentary.\n\nCapture Context: Ensure that explanations of features or points include 'why' they are important, not just 'what' they are.\n\nMaintain Professionalism: Use clear, business-appropriate language.\n\nTranscript to process: {{7.answers.`67c4efc3`.textAnswers.answers[].value}}\n\nProvide the response in HTML format so it can be sent directly via email. Use <p>, <ul>, <li>, and <strong> tags. Dont mention the word header. Just have them in the result. Also do not have the subject, just include the body. have a greater font size for the Meeting Purpose, Key Takeaways, Topics (Detailed breakdown), Next Steps, Annotations etc.\"",
                                                "type": "text"
                                            }
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ],
                                "generationConfig": {
                                    "imageConfig": {},
                                    "thinkingConfig": {}
                                },
                                "system_instruction": {}
                            },
                            "metadata": {
                                "designer": {
